attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LInWLaH5eXq1ZO3JYGL_description
attribs.current:
You were created to
have remarkable fortitude, represented by the
following benefits:
• You have advantage on saving throws against
being poisoned, and you have resistance to
poison damage.
• You are immune to disease.
• You don’t need to eat, drink, or breathe.
• You don’t need to sleep and don’t suffer the
effects of exhaustion due to lack of rest, and
magic can’t put you to sleep.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LInWdUGQoMR3POtd-YR_description
attribs.current:
When you take a long rest, you
must spend at least six hours of it in an inactive,
motionless state, rather than sleeping. In this
state, you appear inert, but it doesn’t render you
unconscious, and you can see and hear as
normal.

attribs.name: character_backstory
attribs.current: Woke up in a gutter beaten and damaged horribly. With a glass bottle jammed into his neck the homeless who found him called him bottleneck. Stumbling around he wonders into the guild looking for weapons and armor and bones he can scrap off the fallen to repair himself into working order.

attribs.name: character_appearance
attribs.current: When he breathes out, steam emits in a shallow whistle. If given a bottle he can fill it with booze. He does so by using a beer tap that is located in his mouth and opening it with his metal tongue which causes beer, pushed by the gas from the cylinder in his body, to flow into the glass. His whole body seems to have a system dedicated to the production of alcohol. On his chest where his heart should be is a handle, inside it is a chest with seperate compartment that serve different functions to cook and hold food in fresh condition.

attribs.name: repeating_inventory_-LJ1TbTkZGU7ba3Ow8yS_itemcontent
attribs.current: These special tools include the items needed to pursue a craft or trade. Proficiency with a set of artisan's tools lets you add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make using the tools in your craft. Each type of artisan's tools requires a separate proficiency.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ1UnQs6LwaklqAdgAH_description
attribs.current:
You become stronger, gaining the following benefits:

Increase your Strength score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
You gain proficiency in the Athletics skill. If you are already proficient in the skill, you add double your proficiency bonus to checks you make with it.
You count as if you were one size larger for the purpose of determining your carrying capacity.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ1YCl0v6QdKKZncTyZ_description
attribs.current:
At 1st level, your years of fighting in back alleys and
taverns have given you mastery over combat styles that
use unarmed strikes and pugilist weapons, which are
simple melee weapons without the two-handed property,
whips, and improvised weapons. You may not use the
finesse property of a weapon while using it as a pugilist
weapon.
You gain the following benefits while you are unarmed
or using only pugilist weapons and you are wearing light
or no armor and not using a shield:
• You can roll a d6 in place of the normal damage of
your unarmed strike or pugilist weapon. This die
changes as you gain pugilist levels, as shown in the
Fisticuffs column on the Pugilist table.
• When you use the Attack action with an unarmed
strike or a pugilist weapon on your turn, you can make
one unarmed strike or grapple as a bonus action.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ1YZiZR6jZw7sNc8jf_description
attribs.current:
Starting at 1st level, you can add your constitution
modifier instead of your dexterity modifier to determine
your armor class when you are wearing light or no
armor and are not using a shield.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ1YkuJfQwOyTMhemi0_description
attribs.current:
Starting at 2nd level, your experience laying the
beatdown on others has given you a moxie you
can channel in the midst of battle. This swagger is
represented by a number of moxie points. Your pugilist
level determines the maximum number of points you
have, as shown in the Moxie Points column of the
Pugilist table.
You can spend these points to fuel various moxie
features. You start knowing three such features: brace
up, the old one-two, and stick and move. You learn
more moxie features as you gain levels in this class. You
regain all expended moxie points when you complete a
short or long rest.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ1ZBJzcQogjeVN1fMk_description
attribs.current:
You can use a bonus action and spend 1 moxie point to
brace for attacks. Roll your fisticuffs die + your pugilist
level + your Constitution modifier and gain that many
temporary hit points.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ1ZPrePErAzPYHBU6P_description
attribs.current:
Immediately after you take the Attack action on your
turn, you can spend 1 moxie point to make two unarmed
strikes as a bonus action.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ1ZWuT4is4DIoSlO1F_description
attribs.current:
You can use a bonus action and expend 1 moxie point to
make a shove attack or the Dash action.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ1Zi6uRGoKnk79Xyz9_description
attribs.current:
Beginning at 2nd level, carousing, shadowboxing, and
sparring all count as light activity for the purposes of
resting for you. Additionally, once you have caroused in
a settlement for 8 hours or more, you know all public
locations in the city as if you were born and raised there
and you cannot be lost by non-magical means while
within the city.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ2IVuoeIGWSq4npqVs_description
attribs.current:
When you want to grab a creature or wrestle with it, you can use the Attack action to make a Special melee Attack, a grapple. If you’re able to make multiple attacks with the Attack action, this Attack replaces one of them.

The target of your grapple must be no more than one size larger than you and must be within your reach. Using at least one free hand, you try to seize the target by making a grapple check instead of an Attack roll: a Strength (Athletics) check contested by the target’s Strength (Athletics) or Dexterity (Acrobatics) check (the target chooses the ability to use). If you succeed, you subject the target to the Grappled condition (see Conditions ). The condition specifies the things that end it, and you can release the target whenever you like (no action required).

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ2Ji1P6hhZCBUAVCUa_description
attribs.current:
When you make a high jump, you leap into the air a number of feet equal to 3 + your Strength modifier if you move at least 10 feet on foot immediately before the jump. When you make a standing high jump, you can jump only half that distance. Either way, each foot you clear on the jump costs a foot of movement. In some circumstances, your GM might allow you to make a Strength (Athletics) check to jump higher than you normally can.

You can extend your arms half your height above yourself during the jump. Thus, you can reach above you a distance equal to the height of the jump plus 1½ times your height.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ3hG7U315JrWTwIxj2_description
attribs.current:
Starting at 3rd level, when you are reduced to less than
half of your maximum hit points you gain your pugilist
level + your Constitution modifer in temporary hit
points and regain all expended moxie points. You cannot
use this feature again until you complete a short or long
rest.

Pugilists who fght in the Squared Circle know you

don’t have to

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ3iWaUY8uWaW4ZZFuF_description
attribs.current:
Starting when you choose this fght club at 3rd level, you
gain the following additional moxie features.
Compression Lock. When a creature attempts to
break a grapple with you and succeeds, you can use your
reaction and spend 1 moxie point to force the creature
to roll again. The creature must use the second result.
Quick Pin. When a hostile creature’s movement
provokes an opportunity attack from you, you can
use your reaction and spend 1 moxie point to make a
grapple attack instead of an opportunity attack.
To the Mat. You can use a bonus action and spend 1
moxie point to make a grapple attack against a creature
within range. If successful, the creature is also knocked
prone.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJ3io5JOXVWAur9pvg1_description
attribs.current:
You have mastered a variety of special recipes, allowing you to prepare exotic dishes with useful effects. You gain the following benefits:

Increase your Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
You gain proficiency with cook's utensils. If you are already proficient with them, you add double your proficiency bonus to checks you make with them.
As an action, you can inspect a drink or plate of food within 5 feet of you and determine whether it is poisoned, provided that you can see and smell it.
During a long rest, you can prepare and serve a meal that helps you and your allies recover from the rigors of adventuring, provided you have suitable food, cook's utensils, and other supplies on hand. The meal serves up to six people, and each person who eats it regains two additional Hit Dice at the end of the long rest. In addition, those who partake of the meal have advantage on Constitution saving throws against disease for the next 24 hours.

attribs.name: repeating_traits_-LJIJxaQu5UVvDykFis9_description
attribs.current: When initiative is rolled, you gain the effects of a dodge action. You may also move up to your movement towards an ally adjacent to an enemy, Moving the ally into the last location you were before reaching them within 5 feet. Neither you or your ally suffer opportunity attacks when this ability is used. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your CON mod per day.
